---
title: Pan-Fried Gammon Steak with Mustard Colcannon and Apple Glaze
description: Golden gammon steaks and caramelised apples might appear to be the winning ingredients of this simple recipe, but it’s the colcannon that is set to steal the limelight. ‘Colcannon’ is an Irish dish, traditionally made by combining mashed potatoes and spring greens with butter, salt and pepper. We’ve given it our own twist by adding wholegrain mustard to the recipe.
